author: Amber Stegall
title: Police: Teen found bound, gagged in wooded area near church
text:
BATON ROUGE, LA (WAFB) - A 15-year-old girl who had been bound and gagged in a wooded-area was found Tuesday afternoon by a person walking in the area, according to Baton Rouge Police Department officials.
Baton Rouge Police investigators say the girl had been tied up in the woods near St. James Baptist Church on North 44th since Monday night.
Police officials say the girl ran away from her home Monday night with a male, but it is unknown if the male is involved in the case.
The passerby heard the girl's cries for help and went to the nearby church to call 911.
Investigators say there may have been three suspects involved. No information about the suspects has been released.
The girl was taken to the hospital where her current condition is unknown.
If you have information about this crime, you are urged to call Crime Stoppers at 225-344-7867.
